currentQuizSentences: [{"分類":"Design","Words":"absorb-2","名人":"Barack Obama","句子":"In a divided world, we must absorb the differences and turn them into understanding.","中文":"（在分裂的世界裡，我們必須吸收彼此的不同，並將其轉化為理解。）"},{"分類":"Design","Words":"absorb-3","名人":"Steve Jobs","句子":" To create something revolutionary, you must absorb the past, challenge the present, and redefine the future.","中文":"（要創造革命性的事物，你必須吸收過去，挑戰現在，並重新定義未來。）"},{"分類":"Design","Words":"absorb-1","名人":"Barack Obama","句子":"A great leader absorbs criticism, not as a wound, but as a lesson to grow stronger.","中文":"（偉大的領袖吸收批評，不是當作傷害，而是當作讓自己更強大的課程。）"},{"分類":"Design","Words":"absorb-4","名人":"Steve Jobs","句子":"Your mind is like a sponge—be careful what you absorb, because it shapes what you create.","中文":"（你的思維就像海綿——小心你吸收的東西，因為它決定了你創造的事物。）"},{"分類":"Design","Words":"aerodynamically-3","名人":"NASA","句子":"Spacecrafts are aerodynamically engineered to withstand extreme atmospheric conditions.","中文":"太空船的空氣動力學設計必須能夠承受極端的大氣條件。"},{"分類":"Design","Words":"abstract-1","名人":"Pablo Picasso","句子":"Abstract art speaks not to the eyes, but to the soul, revealing emotions beyond words.","中文":"抽象藝術並非為眼睛而作，而是直達靈魂，展現超越語言的情感。"},{"等級":"B2","分類":"daily","Words":"abusive-2","名人":"Mahatma Gandhi","句子":"An abusive system thrives only when people accept oppression instead of resisting it.","中文":"一個壓迫性的制度只有在人民接受壓迫而不反抗時才會存續。"}]
